WEBVTT

00:06.464 --> 00:08.425
[opening theme music playing]

00:49.299 --> 00:51.968
STILL SHINING

00:53.052 --> 00:54.512
[drill whirs]

00:54.596 --> 00:59.476
MAY 2018

00:59.976 --> 01:02.020
Well, you always came and did everything.

01:02.103 --> 01:06.191
I felt troubled after getting discharged,
but working with wood eased my mind.

01:06.274 --> 01:08.485
Gosh, I feel so relieved.

01:08.568 --> 01:09.944
I'd accepted the job,

01:10.028 --> 01:11.780
but Mr. Mo suddenly passed away,

01:11.863 --> 01:13.656
and I couldn't reach his daughter.

01:13.740 --> 01:15.867
I wasn't paid, but it still weighed on me.

01:16.910 --> 01:18.536
I can sleep easy now.

01:19.537 --> 01:21.581
-Want to try opening and closing it?
-Okay.

01:31.257 --> 01:32.091
It works fine.

01:32.175 --> 01:34.344
[Jin-su] I'll go inside
and see if anything needs work.

01:34.427 --> 01:35.762
[Tae-seo] Okay.

01:56.658 --> 01:57.909
<i>Just like in the photo,</i>

01:59.661 --> 02:01.913
<i>she must be doing well, wherever she is.</i>

02:01.996 --> 02:03.498
<i>That's what I thought.</i>

02:03.581 --> 02:05.583
[gentle music playing]

03:09.147 --> 03:16.112
STILL SHINING

03:26.456 --> 03:28.041
[soft indistinct chatter]

03:34.005 --> 03:35.173
[turnstile beeps]

03:38.301 --> 03:40.762
I can just go from here.

03:41.387 --> 03:42.263
I'll go with you.

03:42.972 --> 03:44.224
Go with me where?

03:44.307 --> 03:46.726
To where you're going.
I'll walk you there.

03:48.228 --> 03:49.103
Where do you live?

03:50.104 --> 03:51.481
Just somewhere temporary.

03:53.733 --> 03:55.235
So, where?

03:57.946 --> 03:59.614
I can't believe we met like this.

04:00.698 --> 04:03.326
I just happened to be there,
but we kept running into each other.

04:03.409 --> 04:04.327
It's funny.

04:06.829 --> 04:08.539
Why did you happen to be there?

04:10.166 --> 04:13.002
If you're out for a walk,
you could end up there.

04:14.921 --> 04:17.423
Out for a walk on a subway platform?

04:19.884 --> 04:20.885
[Tae-seo sighs]

04:21.719 --> 04:23.179
It's that apartment.

04:29.435 --> 04:30.937
Am I not supposed to go there?

04:31.604 --> 04:32.438
What?

04:32.522 --> 04:34.607
Would it put you in a bind
if someone saw you?

04:35.191 --> 04:36.067
For example…

04:36.776 --> 04:38.653
-Because you're married?
-No.

04:39.487 --> 04:40.655
That's not why…

04:41.698 --> 04:42.949
I'm not married.

04:43.032 --> 04:44.826
-Wow…
-[Tae-seo inhales]

04:44.909 --> 04:47.161
That's so ridiculous I'm speechless.

04:48.204 --> 04:50.206
I work there. "Empty home care."

04:51.958 --> 04:54.502
I just made that term up, but…

04:54.585 --> 04:57.380
I'm literally just watching the house
while the owner is away.

04:57.964 --> 05:00.800
It's just homes of people I know
who have pets or houseplants.

05:00.883 --> 05:02.719
I'm basically taking care of them.

05:06.973 --> 05:08.850
How far are you planning to go?

05:10.101 --> 05:11.019
[sighs]

05:16.399 --> 05:18.526
[Eun-a] I came to Seoul
only a few days ago.

05:20.611 --> 05:23.156
[Tae-seo] Did you come to Seoul
to do this kind of work?

05:23.239 --> 05:24.615
[Eun-a] I have a separate day job.

05:24.699 --> 05:26.659
This is just temporary.

05:26.743 --> 05:28.453
Then, where do you live?

05:29.078 --> 05:32.832
I know you have a lot of questions,
but we're here.

05:34.167 --> 05:35.793
It was nice to see you.

05:41.716 --> 05:42.633
Tae-seo.

05:44.594 --> 05:45.511
Is it okay

05:46.471 --> 05:48.264
if I keep in touch?

05:53.603 --> 05:54.520
Okay.

06:00.860 --> 06:03.905
[keypad beeping, dings]

06:06.032 --> 06:08.242
Oh… Rael?

06:08.868 --> 06:09.869
What are you doing here?

06:10.953 --> 06:11.788
[Eun-a sighs]

06:18.711 --> 06:20.797
[Na-yeong]
You're Park So-hyeon's daughter?

06:20.880 --> 06:24.592
After Ho-sik was torn up over her,
do you know how many years I spent

06:24.675 --> 06:25.802
trying to comfort him?

06:25.885 --> 06:27.970
Seriously, how could you?

06:28.054 --> 06:30.181
-Na-yeong.
-You should've told me!

06:31.516 --> 06:33.059
[sighs softy]

06:33.643 --> 06:34.852
[Na-yeong scoffs]

06:37.063 --> 06:39.649
Ho-sik suddenly suggested we go camping.

06:39.732 --> 06:42.735
He said we should ask you
to watch the house. [scoffs]

06:43.361 --> 06:46.572
So-hyeon's daughter needs
a place to stay, so offer up our house?

06:46.656 --> 06:49.075
He even reported back to her, you know.

06:49.158 --> 06:51.452
I caught him on the phone with her.

06:54.580 --> 06:56.749
I'm not her daughter.
Don't you ever say that again.

06:56.833 --> 06:58.334
If she isn't your mom, then what?

06:58.918 --> 06:59.877
Your dad's girlfriend?

07:00.461 --> 07:01.546
What should I call her?

07:01.629 --> 07:04.340
No matter how pissed you are,
parents are off limits.

07:06.175 --> 07:07.009
In any case,

07:07.093 --> 07:10.054
-because of Park So-hyeon…
-Don't you mention her name.

07:10.638 --> 07:12.849
My dad died because of her.

07:12.932 --> 07:14.392
[Na-yeong] What do you mean?

07:16.018 --> 07:17.019
Hey.

07:25.695 --> 07:28.197
-[sighs wearily]
-Is that your only luggage?

07:36.998 --> 07:38.332
[suitcase thuds loudly]

07:38.416 --> 07:40.042
-[gentle music playing]
-Give it back.

07:40.126 --> 07:41.419
Where do you live?

07:42.128 --> 07:43.713
Give me my suitcase.

07:44.672 --> 07:46.632
Where do you live?
Is that so hard to answer?

07:50.511 --> 07:52.138
You're in Seoul without a place to stay?

07:52.221 --> 07:54.432
I told you I only got here a few days ago.

07:55.475 --> 07:57.310
I'll be moving in somewhere in a week.

07:57.935 --> 07:59.562
I had time, so I was going to stay here.

07:59.645 --> 08:01.189
So you have nowhere to go tonight.

08:01.272 --> 08:03.191
I do. Why wouldn't I?

08:04.859 --> 08:07.111
Don't worry about me. Just go.

08:07.195 --> 08:08.279
Let's part ways here.

08:09.947 --> 08:12.325
[sighs] This is so damn humiliating.

08:31.052 --> 08:33.054
[phone vibrating]

08:35.848 --> 08:37.934
SEONG-CHAN

08:57.954 --> 08:59.622
We're going to your place, right?

09:02.708 --> 09:04.794
I'll just leave my bag with you.

09:06.462 --> 09:08.548
If I take that,
my friend will ask questions.

09:09.507 --> 09:11.801
-Just hold onto it for me.
-Your friend?

09:12.468 --> 09:14.011
A friend from middle school.

09:14.095 --> 09:17.223
You don't know her.
She went to high school in the city.

09:17.306 --> 09:20.268
No matter who you stay with,
you're the one making this weird.

09:20.351 --> 09:23.062
Like you said, I ran into
an old classmate in a bind.

09:23.145 --> 09:26.065
How could I just walk away?
You would've done even more to help.

09:46.252 --> 09:49.880
-[swipes key]
-[keypad beeping]

09:49.964 --> 09:50.798
Wait.

09:58.222 --> 09:59.724
I have someone in my life.

10:00.850 --> 10:02.602
We're apart right now.

10:02.685 --> 10:04.395
We decided to take a break.

10:07.273 --> 10:08.816
Is he…

10:10.610 --> 10:11.819
weighing on you a lot?

10:14.530 --> 10:15.573
No.

10:17.700 --> 10:18.534
It's because of you.

10:19.785 --> 10:22.288
I'm telling you because I think
I should be honest with you.

10:27.418 --> 10:30.129
-[swipes key]
-[keypad beeping]

10:37.637 --> 10:39.096
[Tae-seo] Put these on.

10:39.847 --> 10:40.681
[Eun-a] Okay.

11:05.665 --> 11:07.083
You can sleep there.

11:10.294 --> 11:11.128
Okay.

11:13.214 --> 11:14.548
The bathroom's over there.

11:27.812 --> 11:30.689
[door opens, closes]

11:48.999 --> 11:50.209
Get some rest.

11:50.292 --> 11:51.168
Okay.

11:57.675 --> 11:59.552
What's all that?

12:00.928 --> 12:02.388
Wood from Yeonwoo.

12:03.389 --> 12:05.724
I see. Are you making something?

12:06.225 --> 12:07.059
Frames.

12:08.144 --> 12:09.395
You should rest.

12:10.479 --> 12:11.689
What about you?

12:13.357 --> 12:14.692
I have something to do.

12:15.401 --> 12:16.986
It's what I was planning to do.

12:30.291 --> 12:31.625
[exhales heavily]

12:34.587 --> 12:36.422
[phone vibrating]

12:42.219 --> 12:43.888
Hey, Hui-seo.

12:45.556 --> 12:47.183
Yeah, it's fine.

12:50.519 --> 12:51.937
Yeah, I'll tell them myself.

12:53.606 --> 12:56.025
He still looks out for Hui-seo.

12:56.901 --> 12:58.068
[Tae-seo] Okay, bye.

12:59.195 --> 13:00.905
He hasn't changed.

13:09.497 --> 13:11.999
PLAYLIST

13:12.082 --> 13:14.293
[soft emotional song
playing over speakers]

13:19.465 --> 13:20.299
[song stops]

13:21.842 --> 13:23.135
You can leave it on.

13:34.980 --> 13:36.357
The other day,

13:37.566 --> 13:40.069
I logged into your account
and listened to the music.

13:42.321 --> 13:43.531
It was my second time.

13:45.407 --> 13:47.910
I've only logged in twice in ten years.

13:50.746 --> 13:52.039
Did you know?

14:08.264 --> 14:09.098
What is it?

14:10.224 --> 14:12.268
If you stay up all night, what about work?

14:12.977 --> 14:13.811
Afternoon shift.

14:22.403 --> 14:24.405
[emotional music playing]

15:54.411 --> 15:55.704
[sighs]

16:02.252 --> 16:03.754
[music fades]

16:14.515 --> 16:16.266
You can sleep a bit more.

16:16.350 --> 16:18.102
No, I slept well.

16:20.688 --> 16:21.730
I slept really well.

16:22.731 --> 16:26.235
Ah… I haven't been able to sleep well
these past few days.

16:26.986 --> 16:29.113
Can I come pick up my suitcase tomorrow?

16:30.197 --> 16:32.366
Can you come by at lunchtime?

16:33.033 --> 16:34.576
Of course. I'll make it work.

16:34.660 --> 16:36.787
What time does your afternoon shift start?

16:36.870 --> 16:38.664
-I leave at 1:30 p.m.
-I'll come before then.

16:39.623 --> 16:40.457
I should go.

16:41.792 --> 16:42.751
Come eat.

16:45.462 --> 16:46.296
Eat what?

16:56.473 --> 16:57.891
You really haven't changed.

16:59.018 --> 17:00.436
What do you mean?

17:01.103 --> 17:02.187
Soy milk.

17:06.275 --> 17:08.527
I'm surprised you're a train operator,

17:08.610 --> 17:10.279
but this is unexpected too.

17:11.321 --> 17:12.740
Oh, that's right.

17:12.823 --> 17:14.700
There was a woodworking shop
near your place.

17:14.783 --> 17:15.826
I remember now.

17:15.909 --> 17:19.788
After getting discharged,
I sometimes got firewood from there.

17:19.872 --> 17:21.582
And I helped out every now and then.

17:22.332 --> 17:23.917
That's how you got started?

17:24.001 --> 17:26.462
Furniture gets too bulky,
but frames are small,

17:27.087 --> 17:28.172
so it was more manageable.

17:31.175 --> 17:32.843
You always find a way.

17:32.926 --> 17:35.012
You might falter and stumble,

17:35.095 --> 17:36.680
but you get there in the end.

17:38.307 --> 17:40.142
That's what comes to mind
when I think of you.

17:40.893 --> 17:41.935
You always find your way.

17:43.437 --> 17:44.480
What about you?

17:45.773 --> 17:46.774
You…

17:47.733 --> 17:49.193
didn't think of me, did you?

17:51.820 --> 17:52.821
No.

17:53.530 --> 17:55.115
I tend not to look back.

17:57.534 --> 17:59.244
It's better that way.

18:05.918 --> 18:07.044
At your house…

18:09.963 --> 18:12.341
I saw a new picture of you.

18:12.925 --> 18:15.344
It was some time
after I'd left the military.

18:15.427 --> 18:17.596
I saw it when I went there
to replace your door.

18:17.679 --> 18:19.389
The photo itself…

18:23.852 --> 18:25.395
just sparkled.

18:26.146 --> 18:27.272
[soft music playing]

18:27.356 --> 18:28.941
That's my last memory of you.

18:29.817 --> 18:31.485
Looking happy and thriving.

18:32.528 --> 18:34.655
I guess that shows even in photos.

18:35.989 --> 18:40.119
I went to Hawaii as an intern then,
and everything was perfect for a moment.

18:40.911 --> 18:42.621
Just for a brief while.

18:45.165 --> 18:46.708
I've been well.

18:47.876 --> 18:49.294
Just not recently.

18:51.672 --> 18:52.548
I…

18:53.298 --> 18:56.218
ran into you on my second day in Seoul.

18:59.429 --> 19:01.932
I had hoped to see you at least once.

19:02.766 --> 19:06.645
But after running into you like that,
I felt I needed to see you properly.

19:08.147 --> 19:10.482
So I waited for you on purpose.

19:10.566 --> 19:12.442
Who goes for a walk on a subway platform?

19:12.526 --> 19:14.319
Why did you wait for me on purpose?

19:18.740 --> 19:20.993
I had something to say to you.

19:22.035 --> 19:24.246
Go ahead. Tell me now.

19:28.625 --> 19:31.670
I don't think I need to anymore.

19:37.759 --> 19:39.970
[breathes deeply]

19:54.067 --> 19:55.444
[music fades]

19:58.488 --> 20:00.449
Let's say goodbye here.

20:02.201 --> 20:03.619
Thanks.

20:03.702 --> 20:05.704
I promise I'll repay you.

20:08.999 --> 20:09.833
Follow me.

20:11.084 --> 20:13.086
[emotional music playing]

21:41.508 --> 21:43.510
-Hello.
-Come on in. [chuckles]

21:45.137 --> 21:47.055
I guess you still haven't had
a lot of bookings.

21:47.139 --> 21:49.266
It seems that way these days.

21:49.349 --> 21:50.392
I put in two extra.

21:50.475 --> 21:51.768
Have a taste.

21:52.269 --> 21:55.647
[sighs] These are such rare treats…
Thank you.

21:55.731 --> 21:57.482
[alarm clock beeping]

22:02.321 --> 22:03.655
[beeping stops]

22:03.739 --> 22:05.073
[exhales heavily]

22:23.842 --> 22:26.762
[Tae-seo] <i>Hey, I saw you were running</i>
<i>the last trains tonight.</i>

22:26.845 --> 22:29.056
<i>Do you mind swapping shifts with me?</i>

22:29.139 --> 22:31.141
[lighthearted music playing]

22:49.284 --> 22:50.911
[phone vibrating]

22:53.413 --> 22:54.414
Hello?

22:55.749 --> 22:57.959
You just need to come in an hour earlier.

22:59.878 --> 23:01.797
I'm the one who's thankful.

23:02.923 --> 23:04.299
Okay, bye.

23:09.387 --> 23:11.598
[mumbling]

23:22.651 --> 23:23.735
Ah…

23:23.819 --> 23:25.195
Water.

23:42.003 --> 23:43.004
[music fades]

23:46.049 --> 23:48.635
[doorbell chiming]

23:50.554 --> 23:52.097
Tae-seo.

24:21.459 --> 24:23.712
[footsteps approaching]

24:27.924 --> 24:30.093
[Eun-a] <i>The sound of Tae-seo approaching.</i>

24:30.177 --> 24:32.095
[soft music playing]

24:56.161 --> 24:59.164
-[swipes key]
-[keypad beeping, dings]

25:22.562 --> 25:25.023
-Uh, here.
-What's that?

25:25.106 --> 25:27.025
They're scones
that people line up early for.

25:27.108 --> 25:29.361
This place only opens twice a week.

25:29.444 --> 25:33.114
Our guesthouse does business with them,
and she gave me two extra today.

25:33.198 --> 25:34.491
I saved them for you.

25:35.909 --> 25:37.244
You run a guesthouse?

25:37.994 --> 25:38.995
Where?

25:40.080 --> 25:41.581
Just somewhere in a historic area.

25:41.665 --> 25:42.999
Here.

25:48.129 --> 25:49.547
Thank you.

25:50.548 --> 25:51.383
Mmm.

25:52.509 --> 25:53.635
Can we talk for a second?

26:12.946 --> 26:14.322
First, what I want to know is…

26:16.825 --> 26:18.285
You said you were on a break.

26:18.994 --> 26:20.578
What exactly is going on?

26:21.454 --> 26:23.915
Did you break up
and decide to take time to accept it?

26:23.999 --> 26:26.209
Or are you taking time to work it out?

26:26.293 --> 26:27.585
We both see it differently.

26:27.669 --> 26:29.421
How you see it is what matters.

26:29.504 --> 26:32.215
I don't care about who he is
or how he sees it.

26:32.299 --> 26:34.092
Why do you want to know?

26:34.175 --> 26:36.469
If you're trying to work things out,
as your once…

26:39.764 --> 26:42.225
as your once close friend,

26:43.393 --> 26:45.478
I was wondering if I was crossing a line.

26:48.064 --> 26:49.566
Even just facing you right now

26:50.859 --> 26:51.776
isn't easy for me.

26:52.569 --> 26:53.737
For me, it's over.

26:55.739 --> 26:57.741
But I did make the decision on my own.

26:58.325 --> 27:01.703
I thought we both needed time
to come to terms with it.

27:02.287 --> 27:04.456
But after hearing you now,
I was just putting it off.

27:05.915 --> 27:08.501
But let's stop talking about this.

27:09.919 --> 27:12.922
Talking about my breakup with you
just isn't right.

27:14.007 --> 27:17.218
I've only shown you my worst,
so I feel really bad…

27:17.302 --> 27:19.888
If you know where you stand,
I'll get to the point.

27:20.555 --> 27:22.474
I have to go to work,
so I'll keep it short.

27:23.975 --> 27:25.769
Stay here today and tomorrow.

27:26.394 --> 27:28.313
I told you I have a place to stay.

27:28.396 --> 27:31.900
After night shift tonight, I'll sleep
at the dorms for morning shift tomorrow.

27:32.609 --> 27:34.194
Then, I'm off to Yeonwoo after work.

27:34.277 --> 27:36.363
That's why I spoke to Hui-seo yesterday.

27:37.364 --> 27:38.698
I have to go see my grandma.

27:39.282 --> 27:40.158
Did something happen?

27:41.076 --> 27:41.993
It's no big deal.

27:43.119 --> 27:45.914
After I stay overnight in Yeonwoo,
I'm going straight to work.

27:45.997 --> 27:47.707
You said you did empty house care?

27:49.000 --> 27:50.293
It'll be empty for two days.

27:51.920 --> 27:54.422
I only do it if they have companions
like plants or pets.

27:55.340 --> 27:56.841
Don't make it empty for my sake.

28:01.679 --> 28:02.889
The definition of "companion."

28:05.767 --> 28:07.685
"A partner or a friend."

28:09.687 --> 28:10.772
My companion being…

28:12.148 --> 28:13.400
my friend, as in you.

28:14.692 --> 28:15.985
Look after yourself.

28:17.487 --> 28:20.240
Maybe sleep in all day while I'm not here.

28:20.323 --> 28:22.325
You said you hadn't slept well these days.

28:22.409 --> 28:24.411
[gentle music playing]

28:28.456 --> 28:30.500
I'm sure you've been
giving it your all in life.

28:31.835 --> 28:33.711
And you're just at a brief standstill.

28:34.337 --> 28:36.172
You'll find your way again.

28:36.256 --> 28:38.633
As the next step,
just rest fully for two days,

28:38.716 --> 28:39.843
and then go back

28:41.428 --> 28:42.971
to living at your own pace.

28:45.181 --> 28:47.225
I really did give it my all.

28:48.268 --> 28:50.895
Like I told you,
I didn't waste a single moment of my time.

28:55.191 --> 28:57.318
Well, it's no trouble for me at all,

28:58.445 --> 28:59.738
so don't feel bad.

29:01.322 --> 29:03.032
I bought plenty of water,

29:04.826 --> 29:07.370
so don't bother bringing your own.

29:12.959 --> 29:14.002
Thank you.

29:16.171 --> 29:17.881
I'll try to get plenty of rest.

29:31.853 --> 29:34.647
[music fades]

29:34.731 --> 29:38.610
PHONE OFF
SAFETY ON

29:42.447 --> 29:44.199
[Tae-seo]
<i>This is the passcode for the door.</i>

29:44.282 --> 29:45.158
<i>It's 4675.</i>

29:45.700 --> 29:46.618
[camera clicks]

29:46.701 --> 29:49.871
<i>I bought some food and butane canisters.</i>
<i>Make sure you eat.</i>

29:52.957 --> 29:53.958
[sighs]

29:55.668 --> 29:57.128
[Eun-a] <i>Let's air out the room.</i>

30:01.591 --> 30:03.593
[slow instrumental music playing]

30:06.429 --> 30:08.973
[Tae-seo] <i>These should fit you too.</i>
<i>They're magic.</i>

30:10.016 --> 30:11.100
[chuckles softly]

30:12.018 --> 30:15.355
These are magic shorts.
They fit in middle school and as an adult.

30:15.438 --> 30:17.732
They always fit perfectly. It's amazing.

31:12.245 --> 31:13.913
Tae-seo's home.

31:16.165 --> 31:17.625
[chuckles softly]

31:31.014 --> 31:32.015
[music ends]

31:45.111 --> 31:46.946
[alarm ringing]

31:54.329 --> 31:55.330
[sighs]

31:56.497 --> 31:57.707
I'm late.

32:04.714 --> 32:05.715
[sighs wearily]

32:05.798 --> 32:07.467
[pleasant music playing]

32:34.535 --> 32:35.370
[sighs heavily]

32:36.996 --> 32:38.581
I'll be back.

33:08.653 --> 33:10.989
[sighs] She's settled in.

33:12.740 --> 33:14.158
[exhales heavily]

33:15.243 --> 33:16.869
-Granny.
-Yes?

33:16.953 --> 33:18.413
This is serious.

33:18.496 --> 33:22.000
When I saw you fall at the corner store,
it didn't look right.

33:22.083 --> 33:23.459
Look here.

33:23.543 --> 33:25.461
If it's like, bam!

33:25.545 --> 33:28.214
If it's a fall like this,
you have bad knees.

33:28.798 --> 33:32.468
But if you fall over like chopsticks,
you'll hurt your head.

33:32.552 --> 33:34.429
That's really dangerous.

33:34.512 --> 33:36.556
I just get these damn headaches.

33:36.639 --> 33:38.141
Medicine doesn't even help.

33:38.224 --> 33:40.810
A headache that bad at your age?

33:40.893 --> 33:42.603
That calls for a checkup for sure.

33:42.687 --> 33:45.356
Don't you want to see your grandson
get married and have kids?

33:45.440 --> 33:48.526
Hui-seo already gives me
an earful about it.

33:48.609 --> 33:51.863
I would've already gone
just to stop his nagging.

33:51.946 --> 33:53.322
He nags nonstop.

33:53.406 --> 33:56.200
It never ends with one comment.
He just goes on and on…

33:56.284 --> 33:57.452
[Hui-seo] Goodness, Hyang-gi.

33:57.535 --> 33:58.745
What are you doing here?

33:58.828 --> 34:00.329
Shouldn't you be delivering the mail?

34:00.413 --> 34:02.790
Are you out here working
or making social calls?

34:03.541 --> 34:05.793
Are you threading needles
for every granny in this town?

34:06.377 --> 34:07.837
A delivery should take seconds,

34:07.920 --> 34:10.590
-not half an hour per house.
-[Hyang-gi] I'm going.

34:10.673 --> 34:11.674
Thank you, dear.

34:13.676 --> 34:14.510
Pork belly?

34:14.594 --> 34:16.679
-How did you know?
-Count me in next time.

34:16.763 --> 34:18.806
Just go do your rounds.

34:18.890 --> 34:20.516
-[Hwa-sun chuckling]
-[Hui-seo] Bye.

34:24.937 --> 34:28.232
[sighs] Could you check what dates
are available at the hospital?

34:29.192 --> 34:30.526
What's gotten into you?

34:30.610 --> 34:32.695
You always insisted you'd never go.

34:32.779 --> 34:36.991
Hyang-gi explained it so well
that it was really easy to understand.

34:38.659 --> 34:39.702
[Hui-seo chuckles softly]

34:44.665 --> 34:46.542
Oh… Hello!

34:46.626 --> 34:49.670
You're having grilled pork belly
for dinner tonight!

34:55.426 --> 34:56.761
Pork belly?

34:56.844 --> 34:58.429
[sizzling]

35:00.431 --> 35:02.266
This is really good meat.

35:03.643 --> 35:06.437
Today's meat is very good. [laughs]

35:06.521 --> 35:08.022
I bought it.

35:08.106 --> 35:09.941
They always give me the best cuts.

35:10.024 --> 35:12.860
-[Chang-sik chuckling]
-That's our Hui-seo for you.

35:12.944 --> 35:14.403
[Chang-sik laughs]

35:14.487 --> 35:16.447
-Tae-seo, eat plenty of meat.
-Okay.

35:16.531 --> 35:18.199
[Hwa-sun] Let me go get some lettuce.

35:24.372 --> 35:25.206
Grandpa.

35:25.832 --> 35:27.625
Grandma needs to go to the hospital.

35:30.878 --> 35:32.380
You said she's going?

35:33.631 --> 35:34.632
She said she'd go.

35:34.715 --> 35:36.551
Good. [chuckling]

35:36.634 --> 35:37.468
Ah…

35:39.220 --> 35:42.765
There's this girl at the post office
called Hyang-gi who does deliveries.

35:43.558 --> 35:45.309
She's the star of this town.

35:45.393 --> 35:47.103
The grannies all love her.

35:47.186 --> 35:48.437
I don't know what she said,

35:48.521 --> 35:50.773
but it scared Grandma enough
to get an appointment.

35:51.858 --> 35:54.485
[chuckles] She's a funny one.

35:55.069 --> 35:56.612
Really funny.

35:57.655 --> 35:59.115
She's something else.

36:01.450 --> 36:02.451
[grunts]

36:06.622 --> 36:07.623
Gosh.

36:10.168 --> 36:11.460
Good night.

36:12.670 --> 36:14.005
[Hui-seo sighs heavily]

36:22.180 --> 36:23.097
Tae-seo.

36:24.015 --> 36:24.932
Yeah?

36:28.311 --> 36:29.562
Do you have…

36:31.272 --> 36:33.357
anything you're afraid of?

36:38.321 --> 36:40.406
You know, for me…

36:42.950 --> 36:46.078
it's our grandparents passing away.

36:46.871 --> 36:48.289
[somber music playing]

36:48.372 --> 36:50.166
I'm terrified of that.

36:51.542 --> 36:54.003
Even while I'm working,
when I think of that,

36:55.171 --> 36:57.173
it makes me tear up.

36:57.256 --> 36:58.966
Every relationship

37:00.927 --> 37:02.428
is lost at some point anyway.

37:04.388 --> 37:05.848
There's always an end.

37:06.933 --> 37:09.352
God, is that all you can say?

37:09.435 --> 37:12.605
"They're both healthy. It'll be okay."

37:12.688 --> 37:14.148
Can't you say that instead?

37:14.232 --> 37:15.399
Yes, they are healthy.

37:16.317 --> 37:18.945
Right? Especially at their age.

37:22.156 --> 37:23.491
It'll be okay.

37:26.410 --> 37:29.080
[clicks tongue] I wish…

37:30.581 --> 37:32.708
I had a big family.

37:37.838 --> 37:39.048
[Hui-seo grunts]

37:39.131 --> 37:41.425
And a lot of nieces and nephews.

37:44.220 --> 37:45.638
How about it?

37:46.472 --> 37:49.058
I said three before,
but four might be better.

37:49.141 --> 37:50.643
Let's make it four.

37:50.726 --> 37:52.186
Four nieces and nephews total.

37:52.270 --> 37:53.896
Evens are better than odds.

37:53.980 --> 37:55.273
Not this again.

37:55.356 --> 37:56.899
[chuckling] Come on.

37:56.983 --> 38:00.027
The more the merrier, right?

38:00.111 --> 38:02.446
Gosh, four nieces and nephews
would be perfect.

38:04.532 --> 38:07.034
[chopping]

38:41.402 --> 38:43.404
[gentle music playing]

38:45.990 --> 38:48.200
You've done great on your own.

38:56.751 --> 38:58.044
[Tae-seo] <i>Did you get some rest?</i>

39:07.928 --> 39:09.221
<i>Take care.</i>

39:15.728 --> 39:19.482
To ensure your comfort inside the train,
we'll be adjusting the temperature.

39:25.071 --> 39:28.532
[Eun-a] <i>Tae-seo,</i>
<i>I got plenty of rest thanks to you.</i>

39:29.158 --> 39:32.953
<i>You helped me figure out</i>
<i>what I need to do.</i>

39:34.789 --> 39:38.125
<i>I know I'm late, but congratulations</i>
<i>on becoming self-reliant.</i>

40:04.276 --> 40:05.403
[chuckles softly]

40:23.129 --> 40:24.463
I'll take that.

40:34.098 --> 40:35.599
It's been well preserved.

40:35.683 --> 40:37.101
You can leave margins like this.

40:37.184 --> 40:38.727
Or if you make the frame thicker,

40:38.811 --> 40:41.188
that makes it look embraced,
which is quite nice too.

40:41.814 --> 40:42.648
Oh…

40:43.274 --> 40:46.777
Embraced… I like that.

40:47.361 --> 40:50.197
All five are the same size,
so it should save time.

40:50.281 --> 40:54.201
Then, can it be done quickly?
The reopening's next month.

40:54.285 --> 40:56.662
But we still need to wait
three more times.

40:57.246 --> 40:58.664
Three more times?

40:58.747 --> 41:00.082
One day for gluing,

41:00.166 --> 41:02.626
half a day for the edges,
and a day for oiling.

41:02.710 --> 41:06.005
You have to wait for these three,
no matter what.

41:06.088 --> 41:07.131
I see.

41:07.965 --> 41:09.383
Three moments of waiting?

41:16.599 --> 41:17.725
Oh?

41:17.808 --> 41:18.934
Why isn't this…

41:19.018 --> 41:20.352
[keys jingling]

41:24.148 --> 41:26.150
[sentimental music playing]

41:30.863 --> 41:32.531
[Eun-a] <i>This is a bit hard to open.</i>

41:41.165 --> 41:42.374
[A-sol] Is this the wrong key?

41:48.589 --> 41:49.423
Sorry.

41:58.140 --> 42:00.100
[Eun-a] <i>It's going to be</i>
<i>another hot day today.</i>

42:08.234 --> 42:11.153
<i>I'm seeing the Hangang River</i>
<i>for the first time with Yeon Tae-seo.</i>

42:11.237 --> 42:12.738
<i>Merry early Christmas.</i>

42:22.331 --> 42:23.624
[breath trembling]

42:26.794 --> 42:28.212
[A-sol] Excuse me?

42:29.797 --> 42:32.216
Sorry, just out of nowhere…

42:32.299 --> 42:33.509
[music fades]

42:34.677 --> 42:37.638
[A-sol] Unexpected memories
just suddenly hit you, didn't they?

42:37.721 --> 42:40.683
Yes, they were just so vivid…

42:40.766 --> 42:41.600
[A-sol] Uh…

42:42.476 --> 42:44.311
Old houses will do that to you.

42:45.479 --> 42:47.481
Someone even remembered
the face of their mother,

42:47.565 --> 42:49.275
who died when they were 3.

42:50.442 --> 42:54.613
Good memories you had forgotten
suddenly come up to the surface again.

42:54.697 --> 42:56.699
[melancholic music playing]

42:57.825 --> 42:58.909
Ah…

43:01.370 --> 43:02.955
I didn't expect this.

43:06.458 --> 43:10.421
[Hyeong-seok sighing] Mi-ju…

43:10.504 --> 43:14.216
She kept bailing on me,
so I thought it was weird.

43:14.300 --> 43:16.719
But she was…

43:18.846 --> 43:19.763
That horrible…

43:19.847 --> 43:21.432
[Tae-seo exhales heavily]

43:22.474 --> 43:24.893
I was really serious this time.

43:26.395 --> 43:30.482
Have you ever seen me
date someone for over three months?

43:31.984 --> 43:35.029
I really liked her a lot.

43:43.662 --> 43:44.830
Sorry.

43:46.582 --> 43:48.584
How can you get over that?

43:48.667 --> 43:52.463
I was so good to her.

43:52.546 --> 43:54.173
[sighs] God, this is driving me crazy.

43:54.757 --> 43:55.758
Exactly.

43:57.134 --> 44:00.929
I asked her to give me more time.

44:02.056 --> 44:03.390
[Tae-seo exhales heavily]

44:03.474 --> 44:08.479
[Hyeong-seok crying] You can't just
cut someone out completely like that.

44:10.731 --> 44:14.068
She wasn't having it.

44:14.151 --> 44:17.738
Breaking up completely
without taking a break…

44:24.370 --> 44:26.705
[sighs] That's the best.

44:34.922 --> 44:36.632
Go back inside.

44:38.092 --> 44:39.343
Don't come out.

44:41.011 --> 44:43.013
Go back in.

44:44.056 --> 44:46.058
[soft pensive music playing]

44:47.976 --> 44:48.811
[sighs wearily]

44:54.024 --> 44:55.067
[grunts]

44:56.944 --> 44:58.195
[exhales heavily]

44:59.029 --> 45:00.447
[mumbles] Eun-a…

45:03.450 --> 45:04.868
[sighs]

45:35.941 --> 45:37.025
[music fades]

45:37.109 --> 45:39.611
-I'll just take a quick look inside.
-Mmm-hmm.

45:40.195 --> 45:43.031
It's a good price,
and it's close to the guesthouse.

45:43.991 --> 45:45.868
I can move in after two weeks, right?

45:46.535 --> 45:47.911
Yeah, two weeks at the latest.

45:47.995 --> 45:49.621
So you've made up your mind?

45:50.414 --> 45:51.457
-Yes.
-[chuckles]

45:52.124 --> 45:53.709
When I first met you,

45:53.792 --> 45:57.754
it felt like you'd come here on a whim,
so I wasn't expecting you to call.

45:58.881 --> 46:00.757
-It's this house right here.
-Ah.

46:00.841 --> 46:02.593
-Just go further inside.
-Okay.

46:14.813 --> 46:16.607
[Ho-sik] My goodness.

46:17.774 --> 46:19.067
How could you leave like that?

46:20.319 --> 46:22.154
Na-yeong, Eun-a's here.

46:22.863 --> 46:24.072
Come in.

46:26.408 --> 46:28.076
Cheers.

46:31.788 --> 46:32.623
Gosh,

46:32.706 --> 46:34.750
I feel so much better now.

46:35.334 --> 46:36.585
It was nothing,

46:36.668 --> 46:39.296
but it was made into something,
so imagine how upset I was.

46:39.379 --> 46:41.632
I spun all kinds of stories
about how we met.

46:42.299 --> 46:43.592
You should've told me.

46:43.675 --> 46:46.470
I wouldn't have made such a fuss.
I'd only be a little mad.

46:46.553 --> 46:47.638
Hey…

46:47.721 --> 46:51.058
I'm more angry about you lying to me.

46:51.141 --> 46:54.019
There's nothing worse
than lying to your spouse.

46:54.102 --> 46:57.147
You lay it all out,
fight about it, and then make up.

46:57.231 --> 46:59.358
-That's how a marriage works, got it?
-[Ho-sik groans]

46:59.441 --> 47:01.777
Hey, if I had told you,
you would've never met Eun-a.

47:01.860 --> 47:03.403
-Just eat, okay?
-[Eun-a] Thanks to me,

47:03.487 --> 47:05.948
-you had a nice stay at our hotel.
-Exactly.

47:06.907 --> 47:09.701
I admit it. I owe you big time.

47:09.785 --> 47:13.330
Ah, we'd even taken Rael out with us.

47:13.413 --> 47:14.498
[whines]

47:16.917 --> 47:18.418
[Ho-sik chuckles softly]

47:18.502 --> 47:20.295
How long should we be away for?

47:21.255 --> 47:22.673
We'll do whatever you want.

47:22.756 --> 47:24.091
How many days do you need?

47:26.552 --> 47:28.136
-[Ho-sik groans]
-Let's go back!

47:28.220 --> 47:29.513
-[Ho-sik] When?
-Tomorrow.

47:29.596 --> 47:32.224
-[Ho-sik chuckling]
-[Na-yeong laughs]

47:32.307 --> 47:35.185
We were headed to a campsite
that someone asked us to check out.

47:36.061 --> 47:37.521
Stay as long as you want.

47:38.146 --> 47:39.022
Uh…

47:40.774 --> 47:41.900
And Eun-a.

47:42.859 --> 47:43.986
So…

47:44.069 --> 47:46.530
What you said about your dad
dying because of So-hyeon…

47:47.489 --> 47:49.032
Don't think like that.

47:49.116 --> 47:52.619
I understand where you're coming from,
but it's wrong to say something like that.

47:53.453 --> 47:54.871
I asked him about it.

47:56.164 --> 47:58.375
What you said was so harsh.

47:59.167 --> 48:00.377
I'll say what I want.

48:00.460 --> 48:01.795
[Ho-sik] That's not right, Eun-a.

48:01.878 --> 48:03.755
Yeah, it's not.

48:03.839 --> 48:05.591
I don't like So-hyeon either,

48:06.717 --> 48:08.051
but that's wrong.

48:10.596 --> 48:12.806
It feels better to say that

48:12.889 --> 48:14.308
than to blame myself.

48:15.809 --> 48:17.686
There's no end to it
if I start blaming myself.

48:17.769 --> 48:19.521
I'd have to go far into the past.

48:19.605 --> 48:20.981
And I can't deal with that.

48:22.316 --> 48:24.192
Hating that woman

48:26.153 --> 48:27.362
makes it easier.

48:28.947 --> 48:30.824
So I'll say what I want.

48:30.907 --> 48:32.909
[solemn music playing]

48:38.290 --> 48:41.460
[Na-yeong] Goodness.
You better go to bed, Ho-sik.

48:41.543 --> 48:43.086
-Let's go.
-No, let's drink.

48:43.170 --> 48:45.589
[Na-yeong] That's enough.
You can't even hold your liquor.

48:45.672 --> 48:47.090
[straining] Get up.

48:47.174 --> 48:48.759
-[Ho-sik] Hey, I'm fine.
-[Na-yeong] Oh!

48:48.842 --> 48:49.801
Sit down, Eun-a.

48:49.885 --> 48:51.345
-Hey, just leave it.
-Don't clean up.

48:51.428 --> 48:53.263
-[Na-yeong grumbles]
-[Ho-sik] Ow, ow…

48:53.347 --> 48:55.974
[door opens, closes]

49:02.898 --> 49:04.775
[Tae-seo] Where do you live?

49:04.858 --> 49:06.777
Give me my suitcase.

49:06.860 --> 49:08.862
Where do you live?
Is that so hard to answer?

49:10.155 --> 49:12.824
Now, I can give him a clear answer

49:12.908 --> 49:15.869
about where I live in Seoul.

49:18.580 --> 49:20.207
What else do I need to do?

49:22.959 --> 49:25.671
What must I do so he won't…

49:27.839 --> 49:29.132
do this to me?

49:36.431 --> 49:37.474
[sighs softly]

49:39.059 --> 49:40.519
I have to do it.

49:41.895 --> 49:43.188
I can't put it off.

49:48.610 --> 49:49.820
After that…

49:52.322 --> 49:54.741
I should go pick up my bag

49:56.284 --> 49:58.453
so I can look him in the eye…

50:01.540 --> 50:03.709
and say a proper goodbye.

50:09.214 --> 50:10.757
[music fades]

50:24.771 --> 50:26.565
[Tae-seo] <i>She left her bag behind,</i>

50:27.524 --> 50:28.859
<i>but I'm not curious.</i>

50:28.942 --> 50:30.569
[gentle music playing]

50:30.652 --> 50:34.156
<i>There can be only one reason.</i>

50:35.282 --> 50:38.076
[Eun-a] <i>Seong-chan, I need to talk to you.</i>

50:54.134 --> 50:56.136
[phone vibrating]

51:02.434 --> 51:04.227
[Seong-chan over phone]
<i>Go ahead. What is it?</i>

51:05.520 --> 51:07.814
I'm going to settle down in Seoul.

51:07.898 --> 51:11.026
I'm not going back.
I've had enough time to think.

51:13.028 --> 51:14.488
This is my answer.

51:17.574 --> 51:19.868
[Seong-chan] <i>I know</i>
<i>you've thought about this for a while.</i>

51:20.911 --> 51:23.288
<i>I'll do as you say, so let's meet up.</i>

51:23.371 --> 51:26.917
<i>We can't break up over the phone.</i>
<i>It should be in person.</i>

51:27.000 --> 51:29.711
<i>You had a really hard time</i>
<i>because of that.</i>

51:29.795 --> 51:31.630
<i>Don't repeat that mistake.</i>

51:32.214 --> 51:33.256
[Eun-a] <i>Repeat…</i>

51:34.341 --> 51:35.842
[Seong-chan] <i>I'll come to Seoul.</i>

51:35.926 --> 51:37.344
No, I'll come down.

51:38.720 --> 51:40.305
<i>See you at the bus terminal.</i>

51:40.388 --> 51:42.349
<i>I only have 30 minutes.</i>

51:42.432 --> 51:45.644
<i>I have work early in the morning,</i>
<i>so I need to get back to Seoul.</i>

51:50.690 --> 51:52.359
TONGYEONG BUS TERMINAL

52:02.452 --> 52:03.912
You really came.

52:15.465 --> 52:17.384
You seemed like a stranger in Seoul.

52:20.220 --> 52:22.764
But here, you're the same person I know.

52:39.239 --> 52:41.157
BYEONNWI

52:43.994 --> 52:46.204
-Throw it away.
-You can't…

52:55.088 --> 52:56.631
I know… [sighs]

52:56.715 --> 52:58.967
…how you must've felt coming here,

52:59.801 --> 53:01.595
but we barely even dated for a few months.

53:01.678 --> 53:03.597
We're better as colleagues.

53:04.306 --> 53:06.433
This whole breakup talk makes no sense.

53:06.516 --> 53:08.476
You never had feelings for me.

53:08.560 --> 53:10.145
It was just me.

53:14.316 --> 53:16.610
It was only a one-sided thing,

53:17.527 --> 53:19.112
so just stay in touch.

53:19.195 --> 53:22.198
There needs to be some back and forth

53:22.282 --> 53:24.284
so my mind will be at ease

53:25.911 --> 53:27.621
and I'll know you're okay.

53:28.413 --> 53:30.165
[melancholic music playing]

53:30.248 --> 53:32.334
We go way back, you know.

53:34.169 --> 53:35.420
It's been over ten years.

53:37.005 --> 53:38.673
[Eun-a] When you…

53:39.341 --> 53:42.177
took care of everything
for my dad's funeral

53:42.844 --> 53:46.348
and saw it all through
without me or So-hyeon there,

53:47.849 --> 53:51.353
I had a feeling deep down
that I would fall for you someday.

53:54.606 --> 53:57.776
You keep saying that it was one-sided,

53:58.902 --> 54:00.320
but you're wrong.

54:01.196 --> 54:03.073
I had feelings for you too.

54:04.449 --> 54:06.284
You were always apologizing

54:07.035 --> 54:08.828
and trying to do more for me.

54:09.579 --> 54:10.872
You don't have to.

54:11.957 --> 54:14.250
You were just trying to be nice.

54:14.334 --> 54:16.670
I don't like someone just to be nice.

54:18.380 --> 54:20.006
I had a reason.

54:21.049 --> 54:22.384
Which was?

54:24.302 --> 54:26.304
Let me at least know the reason.

54:31.142 --> 54:32.268
I really…

54:33.812 --> 54:35.438
depended on you.

54:43.822 --> 54:46.199
Call me if you have any trouble in Seoul.

54:48.034 --> 54:50.078
Let's stay friends at least.

54:55.333 --> 54:56.876
Let's at least do that much.

54:59.254 --> 55:01.798
I didn't come all this way
so we could stay friends.

55:05.343 --> 55:06.428
[sighs]

55:19.858 --> 55:20.900
[exhales]

55:22.027 --> 55:23.028
[music fades]

55:27.782 --> 55:28.825
I put you through a lot.

55:30.452 --> 55:31.786
I'm sorry.

55:32.579 --> 55:33.496
[chuckles softly]

55:34.873 --> 55:36.666
I've known you
since you were in high school.

55:44.049 --> 55:45.175
Take care of yourself.

55:52.807 --> 55:54.601
[soft sentimental music playing]

55:57.645 --> 55:59.272
Never mind.

55:59.355 --> 56:01.024
Just go.

56:01.107 --> 56:02.275
[chuckles]

56:02.358 --> 56:04.069
I wouldn't be able to let go.

56:07.906 --> 56:09.616
Not just for my dad…

56:12.160 --> 56:13.828
but thank you for everything, Seong-chan.

56:17.916 --> 56:20.335
That's what I came here to say.

56:32.013 --> 56:32.847
Mmm.

57:12.262 --> 57:13.596
[music ends]

57:25.358 --> 57:26.651
[sighs heavily]

57:32.198 --> 57:33.825
-You're still here.
-Yeah.

57:33.908 --> 57:34.742
Ah…

57:34.826 --> 57:36.453
By the way,

57:36.536 --> 57:39.497
everyone in our office's photography club
wants you to do the job.

57:40.331 --> 57:44.002
Then again, all we've done so far are
poetry and art exhibitions in the subway.

57:44.085 --> 57:45.545
But everyone wants a good frame

57:45.628 --> 57:47.630
now that it's a train operator
photo exhibition.

57:47.714 --> 57:49.257
They all want the one you made for me.

57:50.633 --> 57:53.136
-How many is that in total?
-Eleven, including mine.

57:53.803 --> 57:55.221
It's at the end of next month.

57:55.305 --> 57:58.099
I'll share your frame account
and tell them to refer to it.

57:58.183 --> 58:00.101
Have them pick
the same size and wood type.

58:00.185 --> 58:01.769
If they're the same,

58:01.853 --> 58:03.521
can you do all 11?

58:04.189 --> 58:05.899
Well, I'll give it a go.

58:07.066 --> 58:09.152
But will everyone agree?

58:09.235 --> 58:10.862
Of course.

58:11.821 --> 58:12.864
Oh.

58:12.947 --> 58:13.781
Hey.

58:14.449 --> 58:15.408
What's this?

58:16.993 --> 58:17.911
[Tae-seo] Uh…

58:18.912 --> 58:20.371
A door.

58:21.206 --> 58:23.208
It's the first thing I made.

58:23.833 --> 58:26.920
[scoffs] What's with this photo?

58:27.003 --> 58:30.089
Hey, you should've taken the picture
so it actually looks like a door.

58:30.173 --> 58:31.758
This is just…

58:34.427 --> 58:35.386
[sighs]

58:43.436 --> 58:46.356
EDIT PROFILE

58:47.106 --> 58:48.983
[slow lighthearted music playing]

59:13.132 --> 59:13.967
[camera clicks]

59:19.264 --> 59:20.723
[huffs]

59:56.009 --> 59:57.677
[sighs]

01:00:20.116 --> 01:00:21.367
[music fades]

01:00:51.356 --> 01:00:52.190
[softly] Tae-seo.

01:00:53.107 --> 01:00:54.609
I'm back.

01:00:55.777 --> 01:00:57.654
I left my suitcase here.

01:01:05.244 --> 01:01:06.496
[Tae-seo mumbles] Eun-a…

01:01:14.587 --> 01:01:15.838
[sighs heavily]

01:01:15.922 --> 01:01:17.757
Eun-a.

01:02:48.181 --> 01:02:50.183
[soft emotional music playing]

01:03:04.113 --> 01:03:05.615
[Tae-seo breathes deeply]

01:03:08.367 --> 01:03:10.453
I knew you'd come back.

01:03:40.274 --> 01:03:43.778
STILL SHINING

01:04:12.473 --> 01:04:14.475
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
